      <Session>
        <Name>DGB1-am02</Name>
        <Title>John Maram, Clara Kusos Darra and Musum Darr doing an Associated Motion task</Title>
        <Date>2022-11-09</Date>
        <Description>Family members John Manam, his wife Clara Kusos Darr and one of their daughters Musum Darr tell a story based on a wordless picture book designed by Vuillermet and Desnoyers (2013) to assess associated motion in languages. The story is about hunting and features people, animals and plants from the Amazon. Many of the animals are unfamiliar to residents of Matukar.

Vuillermet, Marine and Antoine Desnoyers. 2013. A hunting story â€“ Yendo a cazar: A visual stimulus for eliciting constructions that associate motion with other events. Linguistic Department, UC Berkeley, ms. http://tulquest.huma-num.fr/fr/node/46.

Vuillermet, Marine. "6 A visual stimulus for eliciting associated motion". Associated Motion, edited by Antoine Guillaume and Harold Koch, Berlin, Boston: De Gruyter Mouton, 2021, pp. 201-228.</Description>
